==English==

===Adjective===
'''sob'''
#sentimental or melancholy to a great degree (one degree further being "[[sobby]]"); almost but not quite [[schmaltzy]].
#:''Five minutes into the movie and she's already crying; typical '''sob''' stuff.''
#(''informal'') sad, depressing.
#:''Tell me a '''sob''' story, see if I cry.''

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[sentimenteel]]
*Finnish: [[nyyhky]]
*German: [[sentimental#German|sentimental]]
*Polish: [[uczuciowy]]

===Noun===
'''sob''' (''pl.'', '''sobs''')
#a short, soft [[cry]].

